onstrate%20that%20those%20in%20charge%20are%20avoiding%20bloated%20org%20charts%20or%20feeble%20business%20lines%2C%20especially%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceos-explain-the-tech-layoffs-mark-zuckeberg-sundar-pichai-2024-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eturbo-charged%20hiring%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20the%20pandemic%20in%20industries%20like%20tech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20have%20also%20simply%20grown%20accustomed%20to%20routinely%20shedding%20workers%2C%20said%20Matthew%20Bidwell%2C%20a%20management%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania's%20Wharton%20School.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20may%20not%20have%20quite%20the%20same%20sense%20of%2C%20'Gosh%2C%20this%20is%20bad%2C%20so%20let's%20just%20do%20it%20once%20and%20do%20it%20big%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-to-do-after-layoff-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejob%20market%20cooling%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Bidwell%20said%2C%20bosses%20don't%20have%20to%20worry%20as%20much%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flooking-for-work-harder-havent-changed-jobs-in-years-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eworkers%20who%20remain%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20feel%20free%20to%20walk%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20CEOs'%20thinking%20about%20layoffs%20has%20shifted%20over%20the%20decades%2C%20he%20said.%20Prior%20to%20around%201980%2C%20Bidwell%20said%2C%20employers%20tended%20to%20furlough%20workers%2C%20such%20as%20those%20in%20factories%2C%20when%20demand%20slipped%2C%20with%20the%20intention%20of%20hiring%20them%20back%20once%20things%20picked%20up.%20Layoffs%2C%20particularly%20among%20white-collar%20employees%2C%20were%20seen%20as%20a%20last%20resort%2C%20Bidwell%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20big%20change%20today%20is%2C%20'If%20we%20think%20it%20might%20raise%20profits%2C%20we're%20going%20to%20do%20it%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrooks%20Holtom%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20management%20at%20Georgetown%20University%2C%20said%20that%20researchers%20have%20found%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhbr.org%2F2009%2F06%2Fafter-layoffs-help-survivors-be-more-effective%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elayoffs%20can%20decrease%20creativity%3C%2Fa%3E%20among%20workers%20who%20remain%2C%20and%20increase%20their%20stress%20and%20rates%20of%20burnout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%2C%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20an%20email%2C%20it%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bmuch%20better%26quot%3B%20to%20make%20one-time%20cuts%20rather%20than%20spreading%20them%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20reason%20employers%20might%20prefer%20one%20big%20swing%3A%20People%20start%20leaving%20after%20layoffs.%20Research%20has%20shown%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-layoffs-could-harm-productivity-recruitment-reputation-tesla-google-microsoft-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshare%20of%20workers%20who%20quit%3C%2Fa%3E%20tends%20to%20increase%20by%20about%2050%25%20in%20the%20year%20following%20a%20layoff%20%E2%80%94%20and%20often%20the%20best%20performers%20are%20among%20them%20because%20they%20have%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dd0d452b-62d3-4e50-bad2-fe5145cfec2d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EReasons%20to%20go%20slow%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20can%20be%20disruptive%20to%20workers%2C%20it's%20easy%20to%20see%20why%20CEOs%20might%20not%20want%20to%20swing%20the%20axe%20all%20at%20once.%20If%20they%20overshoot%2C%20they%20risk%20having%20to%20hire%20again%2C%20and%20few%20things%20signal%20instability%20like%20a%20whiplash%20hiring%20spree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20the%20cuts%20over%20with%20might%20help%20morale%20and%20trust%20bounce%20back%20sooner%2C%20yet%20the%20approach%20also%20brings%20risks%2C%20said%20Sarah%20Rodehorst%2C%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Onwards%20HR%2C%20which%20helps%20large%20companies%20stay%20compliant%20with%20regulations%20when%20laying%20off%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20moment%20when%20everything%20from%20AI%20to%20tariffs%20to%20government%20spending%20cuts%20is%20making%20decision-making%20difficult%2C%20there's%20a%20danger%20in%20cutting%20too%20quickly.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWhat%20a%20business%20needs%20today%20could%20look%20very%20different%20six%20months%20from%20now%2C%20Rodehorst%20said.%20Plus%2C%20slashing%20too%20many%20people%20at%20once%20can%20make%20it%20harder%20to%20reassign%20work%20and%20rewire%20the%20organization's%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20business%20may%20need%20people%20for%20a%20period%20of%20time%20as%20part%20of%20that%20restructure%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%2C%20it's%20hard%20to%20let%20everyone%20go%20all%20at%20once.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20risk%2C%20of%20course%2C%20is%20that%20the%20people%20left%20behind%20spend%20more%20time%20wondering%20if%20they're%20next%20rather%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethan%20focusing%20on%20their%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20as%20CEOs%20overseeing%20the%20cuts%20might%20wish%20it%2C%20the%20period%20after%20layoffs%20isn't%20exactly%20%26quot%3Binnovation%20and%20growing-the-business%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Scott%20Kirsner%2C%20CEO%20of%20InnoLead%2C%20a%20research%20firm%20focused%20on%20corporate%20innovation.%20Instead%2C%20he%20said%2C%20teams%20tend%20to%20be%20busy%20figuring%20out%20who's%20managing%20whom%20and%20what%20the%20company%20even%20looks%20like%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBidwell%2C%20from%20Wharton%2C%20said%20that%20big%20cuts%20often%20create%20%26quot%3Bhuge%20turmoil%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20trying%20to%20avoid%20layoffs%20for%20several%20years%20can%20require%20leaders%20to%20make%20big%20predictions%20about%20what%20a%20business%20will%20need%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20so%2C%20he%20said%2C%20the%20idea%20that%20businesses%20can%20simply%20cut%20and%20rehire%20as%20needed%20overlooks%20the%20hidden%20drags%20%E2%80%94%20things%20like%20damaged%20morale%2C%20lost%20institutional%20knowledge%2C%20and%20the%20time%20it%20takes%20new%20workers%20to%20get%20up%20to%20speed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20serious%20adjustment%20costs%20every%20time%20you%20bring%20new%20people%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20Bidwell%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%2C%20he%20said%2C%20while%20it's%20easy%20to%20tally%20up%20the%20salaries%20of%20laid-off%20workers%2C%20%26quot%3Bit's%20a%20lot%20harder%20to%20assess%20the%20challenges%20that%20you're%20going%20to%20face%20in%20continuing%20to%20motivate%20your%20people%20and%20getting%20the%20work%20done.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Atparadis%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Etparadis%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20Signal%20at%20tparadis.70.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%2C%20a%20nonwork%20WiFi%20network%2C%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%20here's%20our%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-guide-to-securely-sharing-whistleblower-information-about-powerful-institutions-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eguide%20to%20sharing%20information%20securely%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployers-laying-off-workers-in-waves-2025-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1761902701000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6903b5e90be9845f2dc56b43%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployers-laying-off-workers-in-waves-2025-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20number%20of%20companies%20have%20opted%20to%20cut