ption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Federal%20Reserve's%20rate%20cuts%20may%20sustain%20elevated%20stock%20valuations.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHistorically%2C%20lower%20interest%20rates%20have%20led%20investors%20to%20justify%20higher%20stock%20valuations.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20investor%20skepticism%20is%20also%20growing%20around%20AI%20spending.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESure%2C%20maybe%20AI%20enthusiasm%20is%20creating%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbill-gates-ai-bubble-similar-dot-com-bubble-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estock%20market%20bubble%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20if%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20is%20set%20to%20continue%20slashing%20rates%2C%20one%20might%20be%20tempted%20to%20ask%3A%20so%20what%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20even%20with%20valuations%20elevated%2C%20the%20old%20maxim%20of%20%26quot%3Bdon't%20fight%20the%20Fed%26quot%3B%20may%20prove%20to%20be%20prudent%20advice%20in%20the%20near%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20interest%20rates%20fall%2C%20investors%20are%20encouraged%20to%20move%20out%20of%20short-term%20assets%20like%20Treasury%20bills%20and%20certificates%20of%20deposit%20to%20find%20yield%20elsewhere.%20Often%2C%20that's%20in%20stocks.%20Historically%2C%20investors%20have%20justified%20higher%20stock%20valuations%20when%20interest%20rates%20have%20been%20low.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELower%20rates%20also%20help%20support%20economic%20growth%20and%20the%20job%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20definitely%20not%20fight%20the%20Fed%20in%20this%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Katie%20Klingensmith%2C%20the%20chief%20investment%20strategist%20at%20Edelman%20Financial%20Engines.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20Fed%20is%20pretty%20clearly%20now%20concerned%20around%20not%20necessarily%20asset%20prices%20%E2%80%94%20financial%20asset%20prices%2C%20the%20stock%20market%20%E2%80%94%20but%20they're%20pretty%20clearly%20concerned%20around%20downside%20risk%20to%20the%20labor%20market%20and%20to%20the%20broader%20economy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJeff%20DeGraaf%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20chairman%20of%20Renaissance%20Macro%20Research%2C%20echoed%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20thing%20that%20gets%20overlooked%20is%20that%20you've%20got%20a%20Fed%20starting%20an%20easing%20cycle%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20about%20bubble%20concerns.%20%26quot%3BTraditionally%2C%20you%20don't%20burst%20bubbles%20in%20an%20easing%20cycle%3B%20you%20burst%20them%20in%20a%20tightening%20cycle.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecent%20data%20from%20Piper%20Sandler%20support%20this%20theory.%20The%20investment%20bank%20examined%20what%20has%20sparked%20the%20last%2028%20corrections%20of%2010%25%20or%20greater%20in%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20going%20back%20to%201965.%20Fifty-one%20percent%20of%20the%20time%2C%20it%20was%20higher%20interest%20rates.%20Rising%20unemployment%20and%20exogenous%20shocks%20were%20the%20other%20causes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20Fed%20hikes%20rates%2C%20it%20tends%20to%20slow%20economic%20growth%2C%20weigh%20on%20valuations%2C%20and%20provide%20more%20attractive%20yields%20in%20the%20bond%20market%2C%20which%20can%20hurt%20stocks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22718%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22rate%20hikes%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6903a54ac007ca8c2737f1af%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22486%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EPiper%20Sandler%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Fed%20might%20not%20have%20to%20go%20as%20far%20as%20rate%20hikes%20to%20dampen%20the%20mood%20on%20Wall%20Street%2C%20according%20to%20Lauren%20Goodwin%2C%20the%20chief%20market%20strategist%20at%20New%20York%20Life%20Investments.%20She%20said%20that%20any%20indication%20that%20inflation%20is%20flaring%20back%20up%20could%20hurt%20the%20market%2C%20as%20investors%20adjust%20their%20expectations%20regarding%20rate%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20data%20led%20the%20market%20to%20think%20