%20few%20lines%20prompting%2C%20the%20whole%20scene%20was%20born.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20have%20sounded%20alarms%20about%20realistic%20generative%20AI%20images%20and%20videos%20bolstering%20bad%20actors%20to%20create%20ever-more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbank-account-scam-deepfakes-ai-voice-generator-crime-fraud-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erealistic%20deepfakes%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20nefarious%20purposes.%20But%20as%20the%20masses%20have%20gotten%20ahold%20of%20the%20revolutionary%20tech%2C%20many%20are%20playing%20with%20it%20and%20arriving%20at%20what%20may%20be%20the%20dumbest%20use%20case%3A%20pranks%20and%20rage%20bait.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETeens%20have%20been%20pulling%20a%20%26quot%3Bhomeless%20man%26quot%3B%20prank%2C%20where%20they%20generate%20images%2C%20typically%20of%20a%20man%20in%20stained%20or%20worn%20clothes%20and%20an%20overgrown%20beard%2C%20who%20has%20come%20into%20their%20house.%20The%20teens%20then%20send%20photos%20to%20parents%20and%20post%20the%20images%20alongside%20the%20text%20exchanges%20with%20their%20panicked%20parents.%20The%20prank%20has%20become%20so%20pervasive%20that%20some%20local%20police%20departments%20have%20put%20out%20PSAs%2C%20with%20one%20calling%20it%20%26quot%3Bstupid%20and%20potentially%20dangerous.%26quot%3B%20The%20children%20of%20dead%20public%20figures%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsora-martin-luther-king-jr-openai-pause-ai-video-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMartin%20Luther%20King%2C%20Jr%3C%2Fa%3E.%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc0r0erqk18jo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERobin%20Williams%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20are%20begging%20people%20to%20stop%20generating%20videos%20of%20their%20deceased%20parents%20(OpenAI%20paused%20the%20MLK%20videos%2C%20and%20says%20estates%20can%20request%20opt-outs%20for%20using%20images%20of%20the%20deceased).%20TikTok%20abounds%20with%20videos%20of%20AI-generated%20animals%2C%20from%20the%20viral%20fake%20bunnies%20jumping%20on%20a%20trampoline%20to%20dogs%20ruining%20weddings%20by%20taking%20down%20chandeliers%20or%20jumping%20into%20cakes.%20Women%20are%20sending%20AI-generated%20images%20of%20a%20hot%2C%20shirtless%20plumber%20to%20their%20boyfriends%20and%20husbands.%20Much%20of%20it%20looks%20just%20lifelike%20enough%20to%20make%20the%20viewer%20question%20if%20what%20they're%20seeing%20is%20real.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20two%20years%20ago%2C%20AI-generated%20video%20was%20in%20an%20awkward%20adolescence.%20With%20decent%20skill%20and%20several%20tools%2C%20bad%20actors%20could%20make%20convincing%20deepfakes%20of%20world%20leaders%20like%20Vladimir%20Putin%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-ai-generated-content-scary-black-bag-white-house-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDonald%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-small-business-owners-swamped-by-scammers-generative-ai-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escam%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20impersonating%20them%20or%20faking%20documents.%20But%20the%20sort%20of%20instant%20video%20generation%20by%20prompt%20was%20lacking.%20A%20viral%20clip%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwatch-hilariously-bad-ai-modelscope-videos-will-smith-scarlett-johansson-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWill%20Smith%3C%2Fa%3E%20shoveling%20spaghetti%20into%20his%20mouth%20made%20by%20ModelScope%20before%20Sora%20hit%20the%20market%20was%20far%20more%20unsettling%20than%20deceiving%20%E2%80%94%20the%20actor's%20face%20recognizable%20but%20surreal%2C%20his%20movements%20jilted%20and%20uncanny%2C%20his%20fingers%20multitudinous.%20Videos%20then%20looked%20like%20flipbooks%20more%20than%20live%20recordings%2C%20and%20the%20trained%20eye%20could%20still%20spot%20most%20synthetic%20imagery.%20When%20I%20wrote%20about%20AI%20videos%20in%202023%2C%20experts%20told%20me%20the%20technology%20is%20difficult%20to%20scale%2C%20that%20a%20lack%20of%20coherence%20gave%20the%20videos%20their%20signature%20jumpy%20quality%2C%20and%20that%20it%20would%20take%20more%20computing%20power%20to%20deliver%20smooth%2C%20convincingly%20realistic%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20investments%20in%20the%20tech%20have%20led%20to%20rapid%20changes%2C%20and%20now%20anyone%20can%20make%20and%20post%20content%20that%20is%20visually%20impressive%20and%20deceptive.%20As%20of%20this%20year%2C%20AI%20video%20generation%20has%20evolved%20so%20rapidly%20it's%20no%20longer%20recognizable%20from%20its%20Smith%20spaghetti%20days.%20The%20videos%20and%20images%20are%20easy%20to%20make%2C%20and%20social%20media%20algorithms%20are%20rewarding%20the%20content%20as%20people%20share%20it%20widely.%20While%20much%20of%20this%20content%20is%20on%20AI-first%20platforms%20like%20OpenAI's%20Sora%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-new-vibes-feed-ai-slop-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta's%20Vibes%3C%2Fa%3E%20feed%20or%20on%20X%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgrok-workers-hellboy-hollywood-movies-elon-musk-xai-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ExAI's%20Grok%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20doesn't%20always%20stay%20there%2C%20and%20makes%20its%20way%20to%20platforms%20where%20people%20have%20grown%20to%20expect%20that%20what%20they%20see%20could%20be%20real.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20a%20perfect%20engine%20for%20a%20new%20age%20of%20memes%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Henry%20Ajder%2C%20an%20AI%20and%20deepfake%20expert%20who%20has%20advised%20companies%20like%20Meta.%20Gen%20AI%20imagery%20%26quot%3Bmixes%20being%20able%20to%20make%20something%20custom%20and%20make%20something%20particular%20to%20you%20whilst%20also%20retaining%20a%20kind%20of%20style.%26quot%3B%20It%20does%20so%20quickly%2C%20allowing%20people%20to%20jump%20on%20trends%20faster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20this%20is%20the%20latest%20evolution%20of%20longstanding%20social%20media%20problems%20%E2%80%94%20highly%20partisan%20and%20shocking%20disinformation%20as%20well%20as%20rage-baiting%2C%20exploitive%20content%20can%20rise%20to%20the%20top.%20%26quot%3BIn%20some%20ways%20this%20is%20not%20an%20algorithmic%20problem%2C%20it's%20a%20human%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Hany%20Farid%2C%20a%20professor%20in%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Berkeley%20School%20of%20Information.%20People%20are%20making%20slop%20and%20watching%20slop%2C%20training%20the%20algorithms%20to%20feed%20users%20another%20helping%20of%20slop.%20Where%20the%20algorithm%20does%20play%20a%20role%20is%20in%20the%20rapid%20shuttling%20of%20slop%20or%20pranks%20or%20trends%20to%20many%20more%20people.%20And%20while%20TikTok%20dances%20have%20moved%20rapidly%20through%20feeds%20or%20X%20could%20quickly%20make%20news%20stories%20go%20viral%2C%20the%20lift%20to%20make%20AI-generated%20content%20has%20fallen%20so%20spectacularly%20that%20making%20the%20videos%20is%20about%20as%20quick%20as%20firing%20off%20a%20bad%20tweet.%20%26quot%3BWith%20AI%20slop%2C%20you%20can%20adapt%20really%20quickly%20because%20you're%20not%20making%20anything%2C%20and%20so%20the%20manipulation%20of%20these%20algorithms%20%E2%80%94%20and%20humans%20at%20the%20other%20end%20of%20those%20algorithms%20%E2%80%94%20can%20be%20much%20more%20dramatic.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20sort%20of%20inane%20video%20trends%20point%20to%20a%20larger%20underlying%20issue%20with%20gen%20AI%3A%20There's%20a%20lack%20of%20understanding%20what%20it's%20meant%20for%2C%20says%20Olivia%20Gambelin%2C%20an%20AI%20ethicist%20and%20author%20of%20the%20book%20%26quot%3BResponsible%20AI.%26quot%3B%20AI%20companies%20have%20unleashed%20these%20videos%20and%20largely%20left%20the%20public%20to%20decide%20what%20they%20do%20well%20and%20what%20value%20they%20have.%20Gambelin%20says%20it's%20like%20they're%20telling%20everyone%2C%20%26quot%3B'You%20find%20something%20to%20do%20with%20this%2C'%20rather%20than%2C%20we're%20going%20to%20come%20up%20with%20some%20actual%20practical%2C%20fundamental%20uses%20that%20you%20could%20use%20to%20change%20your%20life%20or%20fundamentally%20better%20your%20life.%26quot%3B%20OpenAI's%20Sam%20Altman%20has%20said%20himself%20that%20people%20should%20decide%20how%20to%20use%20AI%2C%20within%20certain%20boundaries.%20%26quot%3BHow%20much%20does%20society%20define%20boundaries%20versus%20trusting%20the%20user%20with%20these%20tools%3F%26quot%3B%20Altman%20said%20during%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.mit.edu%2F2024%2Fpresident-sally-kornbluth-openai-ceo-sam-altman-discuss-future-ai-0506%3Futm_source%3Dchatgpt.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etalk%20at%20MIT%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20year.%20%26quot%3BNot%20everyone%20will%20use%20them%20the%20way%20we%20like%2C%20but%20that's%20just%20kind%20of%20the%20case%20with%20tools.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20artists%20have%20found%20compelling%20ways%20to%20incorporate%20AI%20imagery%20into%20their%20work%20and%20push%20the%20boundaries%20of%20what%20they%20could%20do%20alone%20or%20on%20a%20tight%20budget%2C%20but%20most%20people%20don't%20have%20the%20time%20or%20ideas%20to%20do%20so.%20That%20leads%20to%20using%20gen%20AI%20for%20the%20easy-lift%20mimicking%20of%20social%20media%20trends%3B%20they%20take%20seconds%20to%20make%2C%20garner%20attention%2C%20and%20briefly%20entertain.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20that%20those%20stupid%20uses%20are%20the%20easiest%20ones%20to%20wrap%20our%20minds%20around%2C%26quot%3B%20Gambelin%20says%2C%20whereas%20a%20more%20philosophical%20question%20around%20the%20technology%20asks%3A%20%26quot%3BWhat%20is%20the%20problem%20that%20we're%20trying%20to%20solve%20here%20with%20AI%20generated%20video%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20sort%20of%20AI%20videos%20are%20all%20over%20social%20media%20right%20now%2C%20but%20their%20prominence%20could%20fade.%20%26quot%3BRight%20now%20we%20may%20be%20having%20the%20novelty%20effect%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Farid.%20Generated%20AI%20videos%20catch%20the%20eye%20because%20they%20can%20create%20scenarios%20we've%20never%20before%20encountered.%20%26quot%3BI%20could%20also%20see%20that%20getting%20to%20a%20point%20where%20after%20the%20novelty%20wears%20off%2C%20which%20won't%20take%20long%2C%20you%20would%20be%20like%2C%20'all%20right%2C%20this%20is%20really%20dumb.'%26quot%3B%20AI%20can%20mimic%20great%20physical%20feats%20or%20cute%20dogs%2C%20but%20the%20videos%20don't%20always%20build%20emotional%20connection.%20We%20want%20to%20see%20people%20dance%20and%20do%20back%20flips%20and%20watch%20silly%20animals%20because%20those%20images%20are%20real%20parts%20of%20life%20that%20we%20didn't%20get%20to%20experience%3A%20that's%20the%20ethos%20behind%20pics%20or%20it%20didn't%20happen%20and%20the%20drive%20behind%20urge%20we%20feel%20to%20pull%20our%20phones%20out%20when%20we%20see%20something%20remarkable.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20only%20so%20long%20you%20can%20hold%20our%20attention%20on%20something%20that%20is%20flashy%2C%20rather%20than%20something%20that's%20authentic%2C%26quot%3B%20Gambelin%20says.%20But%20in%20trying%20to%20hold%20our%20eyes%20online%2C%20the%20content%20might%20only%20get%20worse.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20race%20to%20the%20bottom%20in%20terms%20of%20novelty.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Famanda-hoover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAmanda%20Hoover%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%20covering%20the%20tech%20industry.%20She%20writes%20about%20the%20biggest%20tech%20companies%20and%20trends.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuse-case-ai-videos-dumb-pranks-sora-tiktok-deepfakes-2025-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2F